
@json
"keys" must be strings :<-- must be separated with a colon (values);
~~> "key" : "values",

@bson (bson)=>{return "binary json";}
bson = "binary json"


@crud
create, read, update, delete

terminal
mongo --> help

@terminal
> help
> show dbs(to show available databases)
> use <database name>

.find() to view or read records in a database
.pretty() easier to look
eg.( db.<dbname>.find().pretty() );

using specific .find() query
eg.( db.<dbname>.find({"key":"value"}) )

you can use var in shell 
eg.(var varName = db.<dbname>.find() )
@note you can only use this once

using cursors
.hasNext()//returns next document if it is true then use .next()

